node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Recovery and Resilience
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. Being able to recognize one of these wounds, and using positive language when discussing it, supports a positive culture across the Department of the Air Force and could save a life. It is important for Airmen and Guardians to seek help for invisible wounds, taking that first step towards recovery.
.
This video describes the importance of Airmen and Guardians seeking help for invisible wounds and how taking that first step towards recovery results in positive outcomes and enhanced resilience.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources
.
Over the past five years, United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has implemented solutions that drive timely, proactive case handling, equitable, informed interactions and decisions, engaged leadership and a supportive environment, and accessible, effective care delivery. 
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. The impact of invisible wounds and can develop at any time, in any place, in or out of uniform.
.
Learn more at: https://go.usa.gov/xszpN
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.title: Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Signs and Symptoms
.
Since its inception in 2016, the United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has been a leader in creating a supportive culture for #Airmen living with invisible wounds. Being able to recognize an invisible wound could save a life. Airman can learn to see the signs and symptoms of invisible wounds in others that they may see in themselves.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. Charles Q. Brown, Jr., & @cmsaf_official discuss how empowering Airmen will lead to success in building the future Air Force today. They also discussed Accelerate Change or Lose, the Action Orders, leadership and followership, how to rise above bias & self-limitations, and the future of the #AirForce.
.
The primary focus of this call was to connect with Airmen across the world, and give insight to how the Action orders, new Air Force missions statement and developmental guidance are being implemented for the Total Force.
.
#RealTalk #CoffeeTalk #Future #Empowerment #Questions

node.text:
A reunion worth waiting for 👨‍👩‍👧
.
After 16 months of families not being able to attend USAF Basic Military Training graduations at Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland, TX, over 1,200 guests recently viewed the ceremony in person. Many shed tears of joy at finally seeing their Airman recite the oath of enlistment.
.
#bootcamp #militarylifestyle 
.
📸 by Jason Wilkinson

Today, we remember #PurpleHeartDay.
.
A member of the @138fw honor guard performs TAPS during a Purple Heart ceremony at the Tulsa Air National Guard Base, OK.

The Purple Heart was awarded to Tech. Sgt. Ariel White, and it was posthumously awarded to Tech. Sgt. Marshal Roberts.

Today is National Purple Heart Day.

First observed in 2014, this is a day to remember and honor the brave men and women who were either wounded or paid the ultimate sacrifice with their lives as a result of enemy action.
.
#purpleheart #neverforgotten

Sittin' sideways.
.
A F-15E Strike Eagle from Seymour Johnson Air Force Base, N.C., performs a high G-force turn during EAA AirVenture Oshkosh 2021 at the Wittman Regional Airport, Wis. The airshow hosted numerous military and civilian aircraft spreading across modern, World War II, Vietnam, and Korean eras, educating attendees about aircraft capabilities and honoring aviation heritage. 
.

.

.
Senior Airman Zachary Peel, 60th Maintenance Squadron inspection section team member, works inside the center accessory compartment of a KC-10 Extender at @travisafb, California.

Continual evaluation and routine monitoring of Air Force aircraft includes analysis of metrics, data systems, inspection reports, inventory controls, requests for assistance, Management Internal Control Toolset, Self-Assessment checklists and any reporting functional community system. 
.

.

.
Two F-35s sit on the flight line during a thunderstorm at @nellisafb, Nevada.

.
#aircraft #lighting #warning #jet #f35
.

.
